@node t-source.asset.com
ASSET

telnet @{"source.asset.com" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'open source.asset.com\r'"} or telnet @{"192.131.125.10" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'open 192.131.125.10\r'"}

login: @{"starsbbs" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'starsbbs\r'"}

Asset Source for Software Engineering Technology, ASSET, is a
United States Department of Defense project to promote the
reuse of  computer software and software-related products.
ASSET, being developed by IBM and its subcontractor, SAIC,
is organized under the Defense Advanced Research Projects
Agency's (DARPA's) Software Technology for Adaptable, Reliable
Systems (STARS) program which was chartered for the purpose
of achieving dramatic improvements in software productivity
while continuing to make incremental improvements in quality
and reliability. ASSET strives to be the national clearinghouse
for software reuse sources and	information.
@endnode
