login: @{"hytelnet" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'hytelnet\r'"}

Explanation

This is a general hypertext browser, packaged with Peter
Scott's database of Internet-accessible telnet sites. Hytelnet
lists libraries, Campus-Wide Information Systems, Freenets
and more. This version was written for Unix, but should
work on any system with a reasonable Curses implementation.

Peter's version uses HYPERREZ (an IBM PC hypertext browser).
This program uses the same file format as HYPERREZ, so it
should be possible to plug-ant-play other databases as well.

The database consists of many more-or-less plain text files,
all in a single directory.  Any text in angle brackets is a
link. Selecting it moves you to the named file. Filenames
are mapped to lower case.
