@node t-eureka-info.stanford.edu
Eureka

telnet @{"eureka-info.stanford.edu" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'open eureka-info.stanford.edu\r'"} or telnet @{"36.26.0.172" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'open 36.26.0.172\r'"}

No login required  Eureka is the new, easy-to-use search service from
RLG.  With  Eureka, any individual or institution can search the online
resources of the Research Libraries Group (RLG), including the RLIN
bibliographic files and the CitaDel ar ticle-citation and
document-delivery service.  Eureka is easy for inexperienced users to
use, yet powerful and flexible enough to satisfy even the most
sophisticated  searchers.

Eureka contains information about more than 20 million books, serials,
sound record ings, musical scores, archival collections, and other
kinds of material held in major research institutions, PLUS millions of
article-level citations.
@endnode
