Meeman Archive of Environmental Journalism

Which Host? @{"mirlyn" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'mirlyn\r'"}
Hit return for VT100 emulation. 
At the Database Selection menu type @{"MEEM" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'MEEM\r'"}

The Meeman Archive is a database covering environmental
journalism. The Archive has over 1,000 entries and grows
yearly. Established by the Scripps-Howard News Service
in 1982, MEEM contains articles from 1980 to the present.
In addition to the articles indexed in MEEM, the Meeman
Archive contains clippings from the Ann Arbor News,
several environmental periodicals, and the  National
Park Service's publication, "Feedback".

The Meeman Archive is located in UM's School of Natural
Resources, 2036 Dana Building. All articles are located
there and can be copied for five cents per page. Please
allow 24 hours for copying. Archive staff can be contacted
by calling (313) 763-5327 or by visiting the archive.


