@node probs "Problems"

If term does not respond to Internet_address.guide:

1) Is Term's connection to the host working ? Try typing in Term's window,
   If you get nothing there's some sort of terminal - connection_to_host
   problem. Nothing I can do about that. Try hanging up and loging back
   on.

2) Is Arexx active ? Internet_address.guide uses Arexx macros to Term's
   Arexx port. Without Arexx running nothing is going to happen.

3) Do you have more than one copy of Term running ? Internet_address.guide
   sends its text to the arexx port named "term". Multiple copies of
   Term will have slightly different arexx port names. Use only one copy
   of Term, or give the version of term you are using for your internet
   connection a special name. Open Internet_address.guide and replace all the
   occurences of <term SEND> with <your_term_port_name SEND> (don't include
   the angle brackets). Make sure you back up Internet_address.guide before
   doing this. Also remember to save Internet_address.guide from your text
   editor as an ascii file.

Crashing

1) On my system running the commodity Autopoint with term causes the
   system to crash, I'm not sure this is a universal problem or because
   of the way my system is set up. Don't use autopoint.


If you discover any more problems please send a detailed description to me
and I'll see what I can do.

@endnode

@node custom
If you know anything about the amigaguide format then modyfing
Internet_address.guide is very easy, just open it up in a text editor.
Remember to back it up first, and remember to save your modified version
as an ascii text file.


Use With Another Comms. programme.

You may be using a Communications programme other than Term and wish to use
Internet_address.guide. This is possible if your other comms package has an
Arexx port and command that supports an external programme sending text
down the serial port whilst it is on line.

The Key line in Internet_address.guide is:

\@{"FTP" rxs "ADDRESS term SEND 'ftp internet.address.here\r'"}

(ftp can also be finger, telnet, etc)

The section you will have to modify is <term SEND>. use a text editor
to substitute the appropriate Arexx port name and Arexx command.

In the 'ftp internet.address.here' string you may also have to change
the <\r>. Term reads this as a command string for sending a carriage return.

If you have any interesting modifications, send me a copy.

@endnode

@node wbench
To open Term up on the workbench window go to the "settings/screen.."
menu item.

Tick the "use public screen" item.

Activate the gadget next to the "public screen name" item. You'll be shown the
currently available screens, select workbench.

exit the screen settings menu by clicking on use, Term will reopen itself on
your Workbench screen. If you want Term to open on workbench every time you
launch it use the "settings/save settings" menu item.

@endnode
